<p></p>.<p><a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/vaginal_dryness_and_vaginal_atrophy/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">Vaginal dryness</a> is often due to deficiency of the female hormone estrogen, frequently associated with <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/menopause/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">menopause</a>. There are many other causes of vaginal dryness. Sometimes vaginal dryness is a result of local <a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/skin_conditions_picture_quiz/quiz.htm" rel="quiz" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">skin conditions</a> of the genital area. Vaginal dryness can also be a feature of systemic diseases, such as 
<a href="https://www.medicinenet.com/sjogrens_syndrome/article.htm" rel="dt" onclick="wmdTrack('embd-lnk');">Sj√∂gren's syndrome</a>. Frequently, no specific cause of vaginal dryness can be identified.</p>.<p class="credits">REFERENCE:<br><br>Kasper, D.L., et al., eds. <i>Harrison's Principles of Internal Medicine, 19th Ed</i>. United States: McGraw-Hill Education, 2015.</p>